                            <comment id="382682" author="adilger" created="Wed, 16 Aug 2023 14:59:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The clients should send &lt;tt&gt;OBD_BRW_COMPRESSED&lt;/tt&gt; for every compressed file read RPC to indicate that they can read the compressed chunks of the file. In the future, OSTs could decompress chunks in memory for clients that do not support compression or clients using GPU Direct on a file. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sending of &lt;tt&gt;OBD_BRW_COMPRESSED&lt;/tt&gt; in read RPCs and negotiation of suppprted compression types needs to be done as part of the v1 implementation, otherwise it will make it difficult to implement &quot;decompress on read&quot; and compression type negotiation in the future. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
